00:23:16,561 --> 00:23:20,232
If he comes to my wedding
with weird photos, they will screw me!

267
00:23:20,315 --> 00:23:22,442
Why would you want to do that?

268
00:23:23,026 --> 00:23:24,444
Because he couldn't have me.

269
00:23:25,112 --> 00:23:27,114
You know what he said over the phone?

270
00:23:27,197 --> 00:23:28,365
I don't know.

271
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:30,158
He went on a trip.

272
00:23:30,242 --> 00:23:31,243
On a trip?

273
00:23:32,536 --> 00:23:33,745
Vladivostok?

274
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:35,247
Why are you going to Russia?

275
00:23:36,581 --> 00:23:38,250
You decided to become a dog?

276
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:39,418
Will you pull the sled?

277
00:23:39,501 --> 00:23:40,335
What?

278
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:43,046
Was he serious?

279
00:23:44,297 --> 00:23:45,382
Why didn't he go?

280
00:23:45,966 --> 00:23:48,176
Fuck it! He really didn't leave for me?

281
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:51,304
- He didn't leave?
- You have his passport.

282
00:23:56,435 --> 00:23:58,520
Why are you always screaming?

283
00:23:58,603 --> 00:24:00,605
I see the light is burning!

284
00:24:01,273 --> 00:24:02,691
Open it!

285
00:24:03,191 --> 00:24:05,235
Didn't you say you were in a hurry?

286
00:24:05,318 --> 00:24:08,530
I have new tenants. Why don't you answer?

287
00:24:14,077 --> 00:24:15,662
What was so important?

288
00:24:15,745 --> 00:24:18,290
- We were at Myeong-o's!
- He might be dead.

289
00:24:18,373 --> 00:24:19,749
Slowly. What did you say?

290
00:24:19,833 --> 00:24:24,212
Myeong-o has disappeared. We were at his place.
Even the landlady doesn't know where she is.

291
00:24:24,296 --> 00:24:27,299
He wanted to move out.
He packed and bought a ticket.

292
00:24:27,382 --> 00:24:30,051
- It's strange.
- Report it to the police.

293
00:24:30,552 --> 00:24:32,679
Why did you call me?

294
00:24:32,762 --> 00:24:34,931
Shall we report? What do you mean?

295
00:24:35,432 --> 00:24:37,934
You can't call the police
because something is strange.

296
00:24:38,018 --> 00:24:40,187
Sa-ra is right.

297
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:43,273
I'm getting married soon. I can't go to the police.

298
00:24:43,356 --> 00:24:45,275
Then why did you call me?

299
00:24:45,358 --> 00:24:47,569
I have to leave with the report car!

300
00:24:49,237 --> 00:24:50,238
I have a question.

301
00:24:51,031 --> 00:24:54,910
Myeong-o didn't call you
before he stopped answering?

302
00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:05,212
I called him often.

303
00:25:05,962 --> 00:25:07,130
He is Jae-jun's driver.

304
00:25:09,341 --> 00:25:10,717
What day do you mean?

305
00:25:11,301 --> 00:25:15,055
On August 19 or 20.

306
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:17,516
Why do you ask?

307
00:25:19,142 --> 00:25:21,853
I got a terribly strange call from him.

308
00:25:22,771 --> 00:25:24,731
I was wondering if he called you too.

309
00:25:27,317 --> 00:25:28,818
What was strange?

310
00:25:29,569 --> 00:25:30,487
He called me too.

311
00:25:31,655 --> 00:25:34,824
And you? What did he tell you?

312
00:25:35,825 --> 00:25:39,621
I don't know. He mentioned some kind of gift.
I ended the call.

313
00:25:40,121 --> 00:25:41,456
I was not sober.

314
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:43,625
Did you get a gift?

315
00:25:47,128 --> 00:25:50,131
Shit, he asked me out!

316
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:53,718
The asshole told me he loved me
and invited me to Russia!

317
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:55,720
Did he think I was crazy?

318
00:25:56,221 --> 00:25:58,723
I get angry as soon as I think about it.

319
00:25:59,432 --> 00:26:03,562
Who let him like me?
Think he's up to me?

320
00:26:13,822 --> 00:26:17,993
You obviously messed him up badly
when he did such a thing!

321
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:21,329
- Punished you!
- Very funny.

322
00:26:21,830 --> 00:26:22,747
I'm leaving.

323
00:26:23,331 --> 00:26:25,584
I'll be in the car. Don't call me.

324
00:26:27,419 --> 00:26:28,253
Well, clearly.

325
00:26:28,336 --> 00:26:32,340
That's how you knew his code was 696969.

326
00:26:32,424 --> 00:26:35,093
And you? How did you know her?

327
00:26:35,176 --> 00:26:38,930
I've been there a few times,
but I wasn't quite myself.

328
00:26:39,014 --> 00:26:40,932
I'm rooting for you two.

329
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:42,851
Shit, there is no "two of us"!

330
00:26:47,397 --> 00:26:49,983
<i>Saturday, 3 p.m. Cabinet number C7.</i>

331
00:26:50,066 --> 00:26:51,026
<i>Pin: 4885</i>

332
00:26:54,821 --> 00:26:57,365
STORAGE AND DELIVERY

333
00:27:45,747 --> 00:27:47,999
BIOGRAPHY
AN JEONG-MI

334
00:27:48,833 --> 00:27:50,418
Miss An Jeong-mi?

335
00:27:51,628 --> 00:27:54,047
That. I'm glad.

336
00:27:54,631 --> 00:27:57,592
I've heard a lot about you.
I look forward to our cooperation.

337
00:27:57,676 --> 00:27:58,677
Also.

338
00:28:00,428 --> 00:28:01,763
I'm looking forward too.

339
00:28:02,263 --> 00:28:03,598
<i>How do you feel?</i>

340
00:28:05,016 --> 00:28:06,351
Very good.

341
00:28:06,434 --> 00:28:08,603
I sleep well. I started working out.

342
00:28:09,771 --> 00:28:13,024
I hear you opened a practice
in Semyeong. Congratulations.

343
00:28:13,525 --> 00:28:14,442
Thanks.

344
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:19,489
I regret not listening to you sooner
when you told me to change my environment.

345
00:28:19,989 --> 00:28:21,866
It's good. How do you eat?

346
00:28:22,450 --> 00:28:24,536
There are excellent restaurants in Semyeong.

347
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:28,581
Does it still calm you down when you hear the rustling?

348
00:28:28,665 --> 00:28:30,375
effervescent vitamin tablets?

349
00:28:33,878 --> 00:28:35,296
I came to say goodbye.

350
00:28:36,005 --> 00:28:37,173
I won't be back.

351
00:28:37,757 --> 00:28:40,593
You are far away, but we meet
once a month.

352
00:28:41,094 --> 00:28:42,429
Is that too hard for you?

353
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:45,348
Distance is not a problem.

354
00:28:46,808 --> 00:28:49,644
You failed to help me.

355
00:30:03,468 --> 00:30:06,221
<i>What kind of shit have you gotten yourself into?</i>

356
00:30:06,304 --> 00:30:08,306
Watch your tongue, asshole.

357
00:30:09,098 --> 00:30:10,308
They're not shit this time.

358
00:30:14,729 --> 00:30:17,398
It is about something small and precious.

359
00:30:18,274 --> 00:30:21,194
- I want to take it away from someone.
<i>-Small and precious?</i>

360
00:30:21,277 --> 00:30:22,362
A gem?

361
00:30:22,862 --> 00:30:24,447
Are you stealing now?

362
00:30:24,531 --> 00:30:27,033
Damn it, I got robbed!

363
00:30:29,744 --> 00:30:30,662
friend,

364
00:30:31,913 --> 00:30:32,872
listen to me well

365
00:30:35,166 --> 00:30:37,085
Let's cut to the chase.

366
00:30:37,877 --> 00:30:39,212
It's impossible.

367
00:30:39,796 --> 00:30:42,048
- You can't get a small one.
- I can't?

368
00:30:42,799 --> 00:30:44,050
Why? I am her father.

369
00:30:44,133 --> 00:30:46,386
You're just her biological father.

370
00:30:46,469 --> 00:30:50,974
A child born out of wedlock
legally belongs to the married couple.

371
00:30:51,057 --> 00:30:52,892
Her father is Ha Do-yeong.

372
00:30:54,227 --> 00:30:57,397
That's nonsense! I analyzed the DNA.

373
00:30:58,314 --> 00:31:00,483
The match is 99%. It's science!

374
00:31:00,567 --> 00:31:02,235
Why are you wasting your time with that?

375
00:31:02,318 --> 00:31:05,321
The match can be as high as 990%.

376
00:31:05,405 --> 00:31:07,824
If the legal father does not renounce the child,

377
00:31:07,907 --> 00:31:09,534
you will forever be second.

378
00:31:10,159 --> 00:31:14,247
Hell! Can't you file a lawsuit?

379
00:31:14,330 --> 00:31:16,624
You can't file a lawsuit

380
00:31:16,708 --> 00:31:18,126
because you are not a parent.

381
00:31:18,209 --> 00:31:20,962
How come I didn't? I am her father!

382
00:31:22,046 --> 00:31:22,881
Shit.

383
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:25,800
What the hell kind of law is that?

384
00:31:26,509 --> 00:31:31,931
You can file a lawsuit only if the parents
then they could not make a child,

385
00:31:32,015 --> 00:31:36,185
if one of them was in prison
or on a business trip.

386
00:31:36,978 --> 00:31:38,229
Was it like that?

387
00:31:41,316 --> 00:31:43,318
It's not. They are doves in love.

388
00:31:43,401 --> 00:31:45,570
The father does not abuse the child?

389
00:31:46,988 --> 00:31:50,408
If he was abusing her, why would I call you?
I would call the police.

390
00:31:50,491 --> 00:31:51,576
In that case,

391
00:31:52,702 --> 00:31:56,122
the best move would not be to sue,

392
00:31:56,623 --> 00:31:57,957
but the mother's divorce.

393
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:01,669
Custody is another matter entirely.

394
00:32:07,383 --> 00:32:08,384
Divorce?

395
00:32:08,968 --> 00:32:10,511
I was with a shaman,

396
00:32:11,012 --> 00:32:13,014
but I didn't discover anything.

397
00:32:13,765 --> 00:32:16,267
I'll go a few more times, so I'll know more.

398
00:32:16,768 --> 00:32:17,769
Anything else.

399
00:32:18,686 --> 00:32:20,939
You're not taking out any more eggs, are you?

400
00:32:21,689 --> 00:32:23,608
Whatever! I'm working!

401
00:32:24,192 --> 00:32:25,485
What is it?

402
00:32:28,363 --> 00:32:30,573
Remember the guys in the rental car?

403
00:32:31,074 --> 00:32:33,910
This time I discovered something.

404
00:32:36,454 --> 00:32:38,790
STORAGE AND DELIVERY

405
00:32:46,214 --> 00:32:48,424
<i>I followed them from the cabinet.</i>

406
00:32:48,508 --> 00:32:51,010
<i>They drove for a while</i>
<i>Bukbu highway.</i>

407
00:32:52,095 --> 00:32:55,473
<i>They went to a motel in Namyangju.</i>

408
00:32:58,977 --> 00:33:02,563
<i>Just when I thought</i>
<i>that I should return,</i>

409
00:33:04,148 --> 00:33:05,483
guess who came.

410
00:33:10,530 --> 00:33:14,325
That! A policeman visiting a shaman
with Yeon-jin's mother.

411
00:33:14,826 --> 00:33:16,411
They are on the same page!

412
00:33:16,911 --> 00:33:17,996
Crazy, right?

413
00:33:19,497 --> 00:33:22,000
I'm not even afraid anymore.

414
00:33:23,167 --> 00:33:25,169
I was thinking something.

415
00:33:25,253 --> 00:33:27,338
If I reincarnate,

416
00:33:27,422 --> 00:33:28,840
I want to be a spy.

417
00:33:29,424 --> 00:33:33,386
Then I'll put on red lipstick
and wear a cool leather jacket.

418
00:33:33,469 --> 00:33:37,056
You can wear red lipstick in this life too.

419
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:38,975
I think Son Myeong-o

420
00:33:39,976 --> 00:33:41,310
he didn't just disappear.

421
00:33:41,394 --> 00:33:43,646
Bass! Me with red lipstick?

422
00:33:45,606 --> 00:33:47,025
He didn't disappear?

423
00:33:47,525 --> 00:33:50,528
You think it's Son Myeong-o

424
00:33:52,196 --> 00:33:53,281
actually dead?

425
00:33:54,907 --> 00:33:58,161
I think these people
they run errands for Yeon-jin

426
00:33:58,661 --> 00:33:59,912
which are outside the law.

427
00:33:59,996 --> 00:34:04,834
In fact, Yeon-jin does not rely
to the policeman's help, but vice versa.

428
00:34:06,377 --> 00:34:09,547
When you say
"businesses outside the law", you think...

429
00:34:10,506 --> 00:34:11,340
Yes.

430
00:34:12,383 --> 00:34:13,968
That's why Myeong-o disappeared.

431
00:34:15,887 --> 00:34:18,973
He worked on his own
because he couldn't trust me.

432
00:34:19,057 --> 00:34:20,725
He also bought a plane ticket.

433
00:34:21,559 --> 00:34:24,145
That means he met Yeon-jin.

434
00:34:25,021 --> 00:34:26,189
And then he disappeared.

435
00:34:27,565 --> 00:34:29,484
And now what?

436
00:34:32,904 --> 00:34:36,491
What did you want from Myeong-o?

437
00:34:42,288 --> 00:34:44,290
Now we are in the same mess.

438
00:34:44,957 --> 00:34:47,960
Which one of them killed So-hee?

439
00:34:55,968 --> 00:34:57,053
Park Yeon-jin.

440
00:35:02,892 --> 00:35:03,726
Great!

441
00:35:05,019 --> 00:35:05,853
But you know what?

442
00:35:07,105 --> 00:35:10,108
Yeon-jin must know
that So-hee is at Joo Hospital.

443
00:35:11,859 --> 00:35:14,862
Do you have proof?
Can you prove she killed her?

444
00:35:19,117 --> 00:35:22,120
So-hee held this in her hand
the day she fell.

445
00:35:22,203 --> 00:35:25,123
PARK YEON-JIN

446
00:35:29,043 --> 00:35:30,378
Why do you have this?

447
00:35:33,589 --> 00:35:34,841
You were there?

448
00:35:36,759 --> 00:35:38,261
And now you were too.

449
00:35:42,682 --> 00:35:44,350
We are in the same mess.

450
00:35:47,645 --> 00:35:48,646
Damn mother!

451
00:35:55,236 --> 00:35:56,404
This is crazy!

452
00:35:57,697 --> 00:35:59,365
I will ask for a billion won!

453
00:35:59,949 --> 00:36:02,285
Let me know when you arrange a meeting with Yeon-jin.

454
00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:03,953
Then I'll give you a tile.

455
00:36:06,747 --> 00:36:08,416
No matter how much money he got,

456
00:36:09,041 --> 00:36:10,293
everything will be yours.

457
00:36:12,753 --> 00:36:14,255
I want something else.

458
00:36:15,131 --> 00:36:17,466
Something else? What?

459
00:36:19,010 --> 00:36:20,636
Confession of Park Yeon-jin.

460
00:36:22,221 --> 00:36:26,350
If Myeong-o got the money,
it is equal to her confession.

461
00:36:27,059 --> 00:36:30,980
He said he would record the whole conversation for me.

462
00:36:34,025 --> 00:36:35,026
Wait.

463
00:36:35,943 --> 00:36:38,821
So-hee's death was ruled a suicide.

464
00:36:39,322 --> 00:36:42,074
Can her confession
change anything?

465
00:36:42,867 --> 00:36:45,453
That's why I wanted everyone to reject her.

466
00:36:46,746 --> 00:36:48,748
Legally, I can't do anything.

467
00:36:49,332 --> 00:36:51,000
I wanted the world to know

468
00:36:51,500 --> 00:36:53,836
what she did and that she admitted it.

469
00:36:55,963 --> 00:36:59,383
I wanted to be for the rest of my life
feels like it's burning.

470
00:36:59,884 --> 00:37:01,677
That pus drains from her wounds.

471
00:37:02,303 --> 00:37:05,640
He won't be able to laugh or eat,
they will have no more peace.

472
00:37:08,976 --> 00:37:13,231
It means you can't get any more
her confession?

473
00:37:15,107 --> 00:37:18,611
We can't even search
the corpse of Son Myeong-o.

474
00:37:18,694 --> 00:37:19,779
What will we do?

475
00:37:23,032 --> 00:37:24,242
We have to find him.

476
00:37:25,368 --> 00:37:26,285
How?

477
00:37:27,286 --> 00:37:28,704
Relax.

478
00:37:35,253 --> 00:37:38,256
What will the findings tell me?

479
00:37:38,339 --> 00:37:41,425
This is a comprehensive test
to venereal diseases.

480
00:37:41,509 --> 00:37:43,678
You have also added a test for HPV,

481
00:37:43,761 --> 00:37:46,305
so it will reveal both flora and infections.

482
00:37:46,389 --> 00:37:49,809
But nothing else, right?

483
00:37:52,436 --> 00:37:54,480
The documents you requested.

484
00:37:54,563 --> 00:37:57,233
Family ties, diploma certificate

485
00:37:57,316 --> 00:37:59,026
and the findings of the gynecologist.

486
00:37:59,777 --> 00:38:03,281
You could have sent them by text.
Who still carries papers today?

487
00:38:04,198 --> 00:38:05,950
I will review them.

488
00:38:07,910 --> 00:38:09,996
- Which bank are you in?
-Please?

489
00:38:10,079 --> 00:38:13,082
I'll go crazy if you're in the red.

490
00:38:13,666 --> 00:38:16,419
Tell me which bank you're in, I'll do the rest.

491
00:38:17,378 --> 00:38:18,379
Miss Moon?

492
00:38:19,630 --> 00:38:20,840
Miss Moon!

493
00:38:21,841 --> 00:38:26,304
I'm so glad to see you!
How long have we not seen each other?

494
00:38:27,138 --> 00:38:29,140
You have become even more beautiful!

495
00:38:33,394 --> 00:38:34,395
Choi Hye-jeong?

496
00:38:38,733 --> 00:38:41,819
Do you know each other? She is my son's girlfriend.

497
00:38:42,903 --> 00:38:44,905
We went to high school together.

498
00:38:45,948 --> 00:38:49,118
I can't be anymore
so warm to you.

499
00:38:49,201 --> 00:38:50,870
What do you mean?

500
00:38:50,953 --> 00:38:53,622
She has nothing to do with you, Miss Moon.

501
00:38:53,706 --> 00:38:55,082
You're going to hurt me!

502
00:38:55,666 --> 00:38:57,752
Let's eat in the temple.

503
00:38:57,835 --> 00:38:59,754
Please join us.

504
00:39:00,254 --> 00:39:01,672
Unfortunately, I have plans.

505
00:39:03,674 --> 00:39:05,176
Are you getting married?

506
00:39:06,052 --> 00:39:07,261
Congratulations.

507
00:39:12,933 --> 00:39:15,770
I will come earlier next time.

508
00:39:16,771 --> 00:39:18,356
Of course. Go!

509
00:39:22,026 --> 00:39:24,195
I so wanted Tae-uk to marry her.

510
00:39:30,409 --> 00:39:31,911
Damn brat!

511
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:35,623
Why didn't you even greet her?

512
00:39:36,457 --> 00:39:38,084
She was happy to see you.

513
00:39:41,087 --> 00:39:44,173
I was surprised.
And we weren't too close either.

514
00:39:45,633 --> 00:39:47,134
Excuse me, I'll be right back.

515
00:39:55,601 --> 00:39:56,519
Dong-eun!

516
00:39:57,019 --> 00:39:59,271
We didn't get to talk.

517
00:40:00,064 --> 00:40:03,025
God, what a coincidence!

518
00:40:03,109 --> 00:40:04,360
Nice to see you.

519
00:40:06,237 --> 00:40:08,906
Can we talk now?

520
00:40:12,243 --> 00:40:13,077
Shall we?

521
00:40:18,124 --> 00:40:20,292
What are you doing?

522
00:40:20,793 --> 00:40:22,795
Why don't you call me?

523
00:40:22,878 --> 00:40:24,797
Do you know how many times I called?

524
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:25,923
Seventeen.

525
00:40:27,174 --> 00:40:28,676
Speaking of which,

526
00:40:29,927 --> 00:40:31,429
do you have something to tell me?

527
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:33,848
What do you mean?

528
00:40:35,266 --> 00:40:36,851
Why did you see Do-yeong?

529
00:40:36,934 --> 00:40:38,853
You really have nothing to tell me?

530
00:40:38,936 --> 00:40:40,521
Don't change the subject!

531
00:40:41,021 --> 00:40:43,566
Who asked for a meeting? You or Do-yeong?

532
00:40:51,449 --> 00:40:53,451
I didn't call him.

533
00:40:55,202 --> 00:40:59,039
Your dear Do-yeong has come
and asked me where the fuck Myeong-o was.

534
00:40:59,123 --> 00:41:01,208
I asked you something too!

535
00:41:03,961 --> 00:41:05,671
You really have nothing to tell me?

536
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:08,632
And what?

537
00:41:09,925 --> 00:41:11,594
Dong-eun is Ye-sol's classmate.

538
00:41:15,055 --> 00:41:17,808
And that. But I mean something else.

539
00:41:17,892 --> 00:41:19,560
For what?

540
00:41:20,811 --> 00:41:22,813
Tell me what you want to know.

541
00:41:27,359 --> 00:41:28,569
Are you crazy?

542
00:41:30,279 --> 00:41:31,780
You are crazy.

543
00:41:31,864 --> 00:41:34,366
You are raising my daughter
as if it were Ha Do-yeong's.

544
00:41:35,242 --> 00:41:36,494
Think carefully.

545
00:41:36,577 --> 00:41:39,205
Did you find out after you gave birth to her?

546
00:41:40,164 --> 00:41:42,625
or did you know before that?

547
00:41:45,252 --> 00:41:46,587
I'm interested.

548
00:41:48,714 --> 00:41:51,842
Are you still married?
knowing that the child is mine?

549
00:41:51,926 --> 00:41:53,177
when you left me

550
00:41:54,136 --> 00:41:55,137
did you know

551
00:41:57,056 --> 00:41:58,140
I want to know…

552
00:42:01,018 --> 00:42:02,144
did you love me

553
00:42:07,191 --> 00:42:10,361
If a vein in my eye bursts,
I won't be able to go on the air tomorrow!

554
00:43:05,749 --> 00:43:07,334
- Ji-won.
- Yun-seo.

555
00:43:07,418 --> 00:43:08,877
Han-sol!

556
00:43:10,588 --> 00:43:12,006
Hello, friends!

557
00:43:25,436 --> 00:43:27,354
Seo-u!

558
00:43:35,696 --> 00:43:39,199
We've been seeing each other a lot lately.
We will become friends.

559
00:43:40,284 --> 00:43:41,619
What are you doing here?

560
00:43:44,830 --> 00:43:46,832
I have a secret child.

561
00:43:51,420 --> 00:43:52,338
I'm kidding.

562
00:43:53,631 --> 00:43:55,007
I came to my friend's house.

563
00:44:00,471 --> 00:44:01,805
Not a parent.

564
00:44:19,531 --> 00:44:20,783
I'm glad.

565
00:44:21,283 --> 00:44:24,119
I am Moon Dong-eun,
class teacher of grades 1-2.

566
00:44:29,875 --> 00:44:31,377
She is my friend.

567
00:44:32,753 --> 00:44:34,755
Teacher, Moon Dong-eun.

568
00:44:41,929 --> 00:44:42,888
I heard

569
00:44:44,515 --> 00:44:46,767
that you all went to school with Yeon-jin.

570
00:44:47,559 --> 00:44:48,936
Did she tell you that?

571
00:44:49,645 --> 00:44:50,979
They are not friends.

572
00:44:51,563 --> 00:44:53,357
And you are her friend?

573
00:44:54,608 --> 00:44:58,278
We are close friends.
There are no secrets between us.

574
00:44:59,655 --> 00:45:00,739
I know her well.

575
00:45:02,408 --> 00:45:04,660
I know what her skin looks like.

576
00:45:11,250 --> 00:45:12,960
I want to ask you something.

577
00:45:15,212 --> 00:45:16,130
Have you ever…

578
00:45:18,382 --> 00:45:20,217
lost something precious?

579
00:45:35,649 --> 00:45:38,318
The Open Day begins.

580
00:47:40,649 --> 00:47:45,654
Subtitle translation: Davor Fröbe


